* Englobe joins the Colliers family
* Landslide in La Baie: Dedication, resilience, and empathy
* Innovative anti\-avalanche barriers: securing a sustainable future
* 35 years dedicated to protecting the environment: Steve Chevarie's story
* A talented young engineer takes flight

The Manitoba Métis Federation (MMF) is the democratically elected National Government of the Red River Métis, also known as the Manitoba Métis. The Red River Métis are a distinct Indigenous Nation and People, and Canada's Negotiating Partners in Confederation and the Founders of the Province of Manitoba.


The MMF seeks to fill **two full\-time Project Officer** positions within our **Energy, Infrastructure, and Resource Management Department** located at **200 Main Street** in **Winnipeg, MB**.

***Job Duties/Competencies:***

* Develop and oversee approved projects;
* Build relationships and communicate with MMF Citizens and Harvester to expand community\-based programs;
* Coordinate work associated with the facilitation of meetings, community workshops, teleconferences, etc.
* Prepare reports, briefings, and letters for review by the Director;
* Research and review all relevant documents, policy, legislation, etc.
* Research and develop surveys and interview questions on climate concerns;
